            <thetext>For some purposes it may be useful by closing a Dialog when User taps on Blocker.
Blocker is shown as greyed, semi-transparent layer behind Dialog, but before application.

Use case:
Selection dialog is a dialog containing a list with selection options.
If user do not want to change selection, he could tap on blocker, and selection dialog closes.

This feature should be set optional: &quot;closeOnBlockerTap(boolean)&quot;</thetext>
